atic Equations: Assumptions','What assumptions can make to simplify the solution to this system of equations?',0,0,0,0,'2015-11-18 00:57:37','2015-11-18 00:57:37',21,87,59),(468,'A Potentially Good Assumption','If you assume that [CH3COO-] << [Cl-], then you have assumed that the acetic acid does not contribute to the pH of the solution of 0.010 M hydrochloric acid and 0.10 M acetic acid.\n\nThis may or may not be the case. For the moment, let\'s assume its not a valid assumption and continue.',0,0,0,0,'2015-11-18 00:57:37','2015-11-18 00:57:37',21,66,60),(469,'Simplified System of Equations','With the assumptions that [OH-] and the dissociation of acetic acid are negligible, the equations simplify as shown above. \n\nThe equations can be algebraically reduced to a quadratic equation in terms of hydronium.',0,0,0,0,'2015-11-18 00:57:37','2015-11-18 00:57:37',21,89,61),(470,'Solving the Simplified Equation','The calculated pH is 1.99. \n\nIf we had assumed the acetic acid had no effect on the pH with hydrochloric acid present, the calculated pH would have been 2.00. Thus, such as assumption would have been acceptable.\n\nWhen would this assumption become less likely to be valid?',0,0,0,0,'2015-11-18 00:57:37','2015-11-18 00:57:37',21,90,62),(471,'Incorrect','Both the concentration of hydrochloric acid relative to the acetic acid and the strength of the weak acid will affect the contribution of the weak acid to the overall solution pH.',0,0,1,0,'2015-11-18 00:57:37','2015-11-18 00:57:37',21,54,63),(472,'Correct. Both the concentration of strong acid and strength of the weak acid are important.','With 0.0010 M HCl (aq) and 0.10 M CH3OOH (aq), the pH would 2.71 (vs. 3.00 for HCl alone). \n\nWith Ka = 1.8E-3 for 0.10 M weak acid (vs. 1.8E-5 for acetic acid) the pH with 0.010 M HCl (aq) would be 1.71 (vs. 1.99 in the current acetic acid mixture).',0,0,0,0,'2015-11-18 00:57:37','2015-11-18 00:57:37',21,66,64),(473,'Success!','Congratulations! You have complete this scenario.',0,1,0,0,'2015-11-18 00:57:37','2015-11-18 00:57:37',21,55,65),(474,'Incorrect','If 0.10 M acetic acid had minimal effect on the pH when mixed with 0.010 M hydrochloric acid, then a weak acid with a smaller dissociation constant will have even less effect (i.e., virtually none).',0,0,1,0,'2015-11-18 00:57:37','2015-11-18 00:57:37',21,54,66),(475,'Background: Calcium Carbonate','Calcium carbonate is a mineral that covers 4% of the Earth\'s crust. It is mined and quarried and has numerous industrial and commercial applications.',1,0,0,0,'2015-11-23 18:42:33','2015-11-23 18:46:13',22,NULL,1),(476,'Background: Calcium Carbonate','For example, one of the main uses of calcium carbonate is the manufacture of cement and concrete, as well as other construction materials.\n\nMany famous buildings and statues are made from calcium carbonate in the form of marble or limestone.',0,0,0,0,'2015-11-23 18:59:03','2015-11-23 19:36:31',22,NULL,2),(477,'Background: Calcium Carbonate','Calcium carbonate is used as a filler material for pharmaceuticals, an antacid, and as a dietary calcium supplement.',0,0,0,0,'2015-11-23 19:02:16','2015-11-23 19:39:10',22,NULL,3),(478,'Background: Calcium Carbonate','Calcium carbonate is used as filler, white pigment, and opacifier in the production of paper.',0,0,0,0,'2015-11-23 19:05:09','2015-11-23 19:38:11',22,NULL,4),(479,'Background: Calcium Carbonate','Calcium carbonate is also a biologically important structural material, being a main component of the shells of conchs, urchins, clams, oysters, scallops, crabs, and lobsters.',0,0,0,0,'2015-11-23 19:06:22','2015-11-23 19:37:29',22,NULL,5),(480,'Scenario','Atmospheric carbon dioxide dissolves in water to form carbonic acid.\n\nMany natural bodies of water sit on rock, soil or sediments that contain calcium carbonate.',0,0,0,0,'2015-11-23 19:13:35','2015-11-23 19:51:19',22,NULL,6),(481,'Carbonic Acid','What type of acid is carbonic acid?',0,0,0,0,'2015-11-23 19:41:36','2015-11-23 20:04:03',22,NUL